{
  "texts": [
    "This outcome is expected because pre-trained LLMs are primarily designed for natural language tasks and not for the specific task of network classification.",
    "In contrast, classical ML models demonstrate near-perfect performance.",
    "For instance, on the NF-UNSW-NB15-v2 dataset, a Random Forest and an LSTM neural network respectively achieve a weighted F1-score of 92.17% and 92.82% [21] while a DANN model achieves 97.81% [22].",
    "Fine-tuning.",
    "In comparison to the zero-shot learning results, both fine-tuning methods showed slight improvements but still failed to significantly outperform random selection or approach the performance of related works (Table. 3 and 4)."
  ]
}